			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				We've finally passed all the contingencies in our Contract and are now 100% officially going to have a house as of April 30th.  Our apartment lease doesn't run out until May 30th, which gives us a full month to renovate and slowly fill the new place with stuff.  The largest problem facing us now is that the Sellers are taking with them the refrigerator, washer and dryer.  
<br />

<br />
I've never had to purchase any of these before, and I'm pretty clueless as to the best place to go to buy them.  I live in the north Chicago suburbs, if it matters.  
<br />

<br />
Are there any sites I should be checking out?  Should I be looking at the major bigass stores (Sears, Best Buy, etc.) or are the small appliance stores a better bet in these cases?  Anyone buy one of the above items recently and have a good/bad experience with them?
<br />

<br />
Your help and advice is appreciated. <img src="images/smiles/smile.gif" alt="smile" border="0" /><br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
