			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				If you can get the Sears don't pay for a year thing it's a good deal, as long as you can pay off the entire purchase when the year is up.  Otherwise they charge you interst back to the date you purchased the items.  
<br />

<br />
Jilaman and I are currently buying appliances and Lowes seem to have the lowest prices.  The same fridge at Lowes is about 200 less than Sears.  Sears have some great deals in the Warehouse/Outlet stores though.  That's where I got my last washer and it works awesome.  Just has a dent in the lid.
<br />

<br />
Be careful buying your appliances at an Electronics type store, like Best Buy.  If you have problems, ie late delivery, out of stock, etc, they may tell you that they aren't in the appliance business and don't really care about your situation.  That's what happened to a friend of mine recently.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
	</tr>
