<br />
I'd heard about ABT, my realtor recommended it, in fact.  Good to know that it's pricey.  I already checked out Jamal, Leilani, but he specializes in dishwashers mostly <img src="images/smiles/frown.gif" alt="frown" border="0" />. 
<br />

<br />
Aedamar, anyone I have to know to get access to that back room?
<br />

<br />
We (well, I'll be honest, my wife - it's her kitchen) has priced out a lot of different styles, she loves to cook so we need a good sized freezer.  A lower-level freezer on our fridge would be cool, but those models cost so much more, we're thinking that we'll just get a standard one and use the extra cash saved to buy a separate freezerchest for the garage.  We don't want to bother with the extra crap on the refrigerator front, that stuff is always the first to break; I can deal with using my Brita pitcher np.  Any major opinions on brands as far as refrigerators go?
<br />

<br />
As far as the washer/drier, all I know at the moment is that a front loading washer is more efficient and worth the extra cash up front.  As the Closing date comes closer, we'll probably spring for a Consumer Reports 1 month membership and check out their reviews on various brands, etc.  
<br />

<br />
Oh, and on the financial front, no worries there. My wife and I both paid off our student loans within 9 months of graduation, own our 2003 car completely without paying a cent of interest, pay off our respective credit card each month and are putting down 20% cash on the home.  We're frugal people who don't screw around with money.  My biggest expense each month is usually Everquest.  If we did do the Sears card thing, we'd transfer the balance to a lower-rate CC or just pay it off in the first month.  0% financing would be nice though.
<br />

