				<div class="postbody">
				Buying on Credit isn't the problem if you buy on 0% interest for a certain period... Not paying the Thing off in time before the deadline is what gets you in trouble... 
<br />

<br />
Recently finished building my first house YAY!!! and bought all my appliances at sears.  0% interest for a year and jsut break down how much you have to pay over that year to pay it all off before the interest hits and make monthly payments to it, not that big of deal.  Sears has some nice crap and I have fallen in love with my fridge so much better then any rental I had.  The side by sides are nice and will never go back.  When you look at them they don't seem to hold as much but they do and you can always find what your looking for with minimal digging  <img src="images/smiles/razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" />  unless the GF hides your food damnit....<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
