				I would buy a new refrig, but for your washer and dryer.  Find a pair that works but is old for about $100 in your local paper.  I did that and the whirlpools I got are like 20 years old.  The dryer works better than any new dryer I have ever seen.  I would light my clothes on fire if  I leave them on high for a long period of time.  Im sure you can find old ones pretty cheap and the old ones are usually build pretty good.<br />
